<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2958] When hbase.hlog.split.skip.errors is set to false, we fail the split but thats it</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2958</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When hbase.hlog.split.skip.errors is set to false, if we encounter an error splitting, splitting stops and exception is let propagate up the stack.  I see that its caught in the new MasterFileSystem class and logged, but thats it.  It would seem processing continues BUT we&apos;ve dropped the edits in the split.  We need to do better (default is hbase.hlog.split.skip.errors set to false &amp;#8211; i.e. skip errors but keep going).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
